The paper discusses the security and privacy issues in RFID authentication protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the analysis of cryptographic techniques used in the protocols, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the flaws in the design of the protocols, which can be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves the analysis of privacy issues, which can be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of attacks on the protocols, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
